{
  "texts": [
    "DiffDock's potential benefits include lowered drug research costs, faster drug development timelines, and reduced risks to human subjects.",
    "DiffDock is still in the developmental phase, but it might significantly alter how drugs are discovered (MITNEW, 2023).",
    "Yet another research presents a novel drug development strategy that uses a molecular fragment-based diffusion model.",
    "Here, the model may produce compounds with high binding affinity to the target protein and minimal toxicity.",
    "The model may produce more varied, valid, and drug-like compounds than other methods."
  ]
}